<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After - REMOVE AND INSTALL - BLOWER
        MOTOR SPEED RESISTOR UNIT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BLOWER MOTOR SPEED RESISTOR UNIT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch is off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower right instrument panel cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601607.xml" xrefid="hl1601607">LOWER RIGHT INSTRUMENT PANEL, HEATER-A/C
                        ASSEMBLY COVER AND DRAIN TRAY</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector from resistor unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws that secure resistor base to the heater-A/C unit. Notice where screws and
                    shield are positioned and remove resistor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601621">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601621" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601621" filename="../figg16/G1601621.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 21. Remove Resistor</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Before installing the resistor unit, make sure the resistor shield is in place (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601621">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold resistor unit and shield in place in the A/C housing. Install and tighten screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to resistor unit.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install lower right instrument panel cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601607.xml" xrefid="hl1601607">LOWER RIGHT INSTRUMENT PANEL, HEATER-A/C
                        ASSEMBLY COVER AND DRAIN TRAY
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
